HEADWORD: Multifariousness
<hw>Mul`ti*fa"ri*ous*ness</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Multiplied diversity.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Law)</fld> <def>The fault of improperly uniting in
one bill distinct and independent matters, and thereby confounding
them.</def> <rj><au>Burrill.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Multiferous</ent>⟦br⟧
